ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project is a Lexical Analyzer implemented in C that scans and analyzes a given C source file to identify and classify various lexical tokens. It simulates the first phase of a compiler, known as Lexical Analysis, by reading the input file character by character and categorizing tokens such as keywords, identifiers, constants, operators, symbols, comments, strings, and brackets. The analyzer also provides real-time error detection with compiler-style error messages and line tracking.

